{
  "texts": [
    "When asked to rate their familiarity with AI tools on a scale from 1 to 5 (with 5 being the most familiar), the dietitians reported an average score of 2.8 (SD = 0.92), while the psychologists reported an average score of 2.0 (SD = 0.67).Manuscript submitted to ACM Selected ModelsTo create the two LLM candidate responses whose quality will be evaluated in the experiment, we use GPT-4o, and GPT-3.5-turbo [2,45].",
    "While there are many models to choose from, we find that GPT-4o and GPT-3.5-turbo are commonly cited in the recent literature [9,28,35].",
    "We intentionally keep this set of models to a limit of two models, as adding more significantly increases the cost of human annotation.",
    "For all responses, we used a temperature of 1.0.For the LLM used to judge the quality of instruction following (the judge model), we use GPT-4 as it is widely available and is frequently used as an LLM judge [32].",
    "As with SME participants, we prompt the language model judge to provide reasoning for preferring one response over another."
  ]
}